ello-dies/</ref>|| Six decades in racing journalism, editor of the New Zealand Racing Annual and Blood Horse magazine and numerous racing books ubcluding Tapestry of Turf.  Inducted into the [[New Zealand Racing Hall of Fame]] ||\n|-\n| [[Shane Dye]]|| 1966 || Jockey || 4 consecutive Golden Slippers, [[Australian Racing Hall of Fame]], [[New Zealand Racing Hall of Fame]] || [[Octagonal (horse) | Octagonal]], [[Tawriffic]]   \n|-\n| [[Bill Hazlett]]|| 1905-1978 || Owner and breeder || First New Zealander to win more than 1,000 races as an owner. [[New Zealand Racing Hall of Fame]] || Eiffel Tower \n|-\n|[[Patrick Hogan (horseracing)|Sir Patrick Hogan]] [[KNZM]] [[CBE]]<ref>{{cite book |title=Give a man a horse |last=Haworth |first=Dianne |publisher=Harper Collins |location=Auckland, New Zealand |isbn=9781775491347 |year=2016}}</ref>|| 1939|| [[Cambridge Stud]] master, breeder, owner||[[Knight Companion of the New Zealand Order of Merit]], [[Australian Racing Hall of Fame]], [[New Zealand Racing Hall of Fame]]<ref>https://www.nzherald.co.nz/sport/news/article.cfm?c_id=4&objectid=10371052</ref> || [[Sir Tristram]], [[ Zabeel]] \n|-\n| [[Colin Jillings]]|| 1931 || Trainer || [[New Zealand Racing Hall of Fame]]  || Stipulate, McGinty, Uncle Remus, [[The Phantom Chance]] \n|-\n| Linda Jones<ref>{{cite book |title=The Linda Jones Story |last=Costello |first=John |publisher=Moa Publications |location=Auckland, New Zealand |isbn=9780908570324 |date=1979}}</ref>|| || Jockey ||Trail blazing woman jockey. [[New Zealand Racing Hall of Fame]]  ||Holy Toledo, Lavaro \n|-\n| [[Sheila Laxon]] ||  || Trainer || first female trainer to win the Caulfield Cup and Melbourne Cup double || [[Empire Rose]], [[Ethereal (horse)|Ethereal]]   \n|-\n| [[Lance O'Sullivan]]<ref>{{cite book |title=Tears in the Wind: The Lance O'Sullivan story |last=Haworth |first=Dianne |publisher=Harper Collins |location=Auckland, New Zealand |date=2004|isbn=9781869505318}}</ref>|| 1963 || Jockey || [[New Zealand 